{"problem": "If $\\sin^2 \\theta + \\sin \\theta = 1,$ then find $\\cos^4 \\theta + \\cos^2 \\theta.$", "solution": "From $\\sin^2 \\theta + \\sin \\theta = 1,$ $\\sin \\theta = 1 - \\sin^2 \\theta = \\cos^2 \\theta.$  Then $\\cos^4 \\theta = \\sin^2 \\theta,$ so\n\\[\\cos^4 \\theta + \\cos^2 \\theta = \\sin^2 \\theta + \\cos^2 \\theta = \\boxed{1}.\\]"}